title: For Sale:  Custom Armalite AR10 SPR carbine.
postcontent:
Armalite Ar10 custom built carbine. This was built to be a 762 version of the MK12 SPR.

The upper is a 16inch armalite with a PRI low profile gas block underneath a PRI full length carbon fiber fore end and topped with a PRI 308 SPR swan sleeve. Recessed into the swan sleeve are a Troy flip up front sight and an arms #40 flip up rear sight. The charging handle has a PRI gas buster extended latch on it.

The lower is an armalite with a rock river arms two stage trigger and LPK, with an ergo grip and a full length A2 stock.

Magazines included are x10 20rd mags (only two are used) and one 25rd mag.

Scope, sling and bipod are not included.

Gun was used primarily on army SDM ranges, and shoots 600-800 meters easy with good glass. Upper receiver was built a 1st Special forces group team chief. The rifle is lightweight at around 7.5 lbs with smooth recoil. 

Will throw in a spare firing pin and bolt carrier.

All in all close to 3,000 in parts and gear, 2300 for full package, plus soft take down carry case. The gun is used, but well maintain and loved. 

I could also throw in the proper height 30mm larue rings, a 250 dollar value.

title: For Sale:  RARE STINGER PEN PISTOL GUN .22LR R.J. BRAVERMAN
location: West Valley Sun City, Phoenix, Arizona
postcontent:
The gun was designed by R.J. Braverman (out of Meredith, NH. stamped on it with USA & serial no.of B00399 - circa 1990. It was marketed initially by American Derringer Co. as Model 2 Pen Pistol from 1993 through 1994.Next, and this sounds like when your gun was made, it was marketed by the R. J. Braverman Corp. (Meredith, NH) from 1995 to 1997, when Braverman went out of business. (this one was the 399 one made) Has small circular saftey F - S ring - only needs to be turned appx: 15 degrees to go from Safe to Fire.
The word Stinger is not on it. Only 22 LR & the above. Only whats underlined is on the item. 
In 2002 the gun was resurrected and built by the Stinger Manufacturing Company in Michigan. That company appears to have went belly-up in 2004.
Two are for sale on GunBroker.com - one is asking $499.99, the other $665.00. Now that is what they are asking, not what they will necessarily get. Used
One is for bid on gunbroker: http://www.gunbroker.com/Auction/ViewItem.aspx?Item=387615368  NEW
Firearm: Stinger Pen Pistol
Caliber: 22 LR
Type of action: Single Shot
Bore Condition: Excellent
Barrel Length: 2 in  Overal length is 5, 1/2"
Finish: Stainless  Diameter 1/2"
Grips/Stock: Stainless
Overall Condition: 98% with Instruction manual. Everything works !!!
This highly collectable and rare little pistol looks like an ordinary writing pen, but 
a simple maneuver, it changes into a ready to fire single shot pistol.  This gun allows its carrier to carry completely incognito, as anyone would assume it's just a pen.  No Class 3/NFA paperwork on this one, since it doesn't fire until you transform it, but it is a VERY simple process to do so.  These are very rare, so don't miss your opportunity! The gun has no signs of wear. See random YouTube of one !
